# Cloudflare Pages headers.
#
# In production the route tiles are served from R2 (which does support real 206
# range requests + CORS), not from Pages — so this /tiles/* rule normally won't
# be hit. It stays as a fallback for any deploy that ships tiles via Pages
# (e.g. VITE_TILES_URL unset). NOTE: Pages itself does NOT serve range requests
# — it returns the whole file with a 200 — which is exactly why tiles live on R2.
# See docs/r2-range-requests-plan.md.
#
# The tiles file is replaced wholesale on each data rebuild (no content hash in
# the name), so cache for an hour rather than forever to avoid serving stale
# routes after a refresh.
/tiles/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600
